@zentree I might have remembered it wrong but I think in regex, a literal dot is given as [.] so no escape key needed

@zentree Oh actually

[^\\.] -> means everything but the dot *and backslash*

@zentree Your regex basically finds all matches from the end until the dot (not including the dot). 

[^\\.] -> means everything but the dot
[^\\.]* -> 0 or more occurrences of above
$ -> from the end of the line
